The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Bihar session starts
                                                                                                               Bihar session starts
                            
	Patna, June 26 (PTI): The month-long monsoon session of the two Houses of Bihar legislature today began on a dull-note with Opposition MLAs maintaining silence all through the days proceedings before the houses being adjourned till Monday.        
	In the Assembly, Speaker Udai Narain Choudhary, soon after his customary opening address, announced the names of members of Business Advisory Committee, besides presiding officers, who would conduct the proceedings of the house in his absence.        
	He then made references to former legislators, including former Speaker Hidayatullah Khan, former ministers Surendra Prasad Rai, Prabhunath Singh, Ramvilas Singh, Ramanand Mishra, Sahdeo Prasad Yadav and Kalwati Tripathy, besides Jharkhand JMM leader Durga Soren and Ramswaroop Ram, who passed away during the inter-session period.         
	Later, the House observed a minutes silence to pay respect to the departed souls after which the Speaker adjourned proceedings till Monday.        
	Unlike previous sessions when the House witnessed rowdy scenes with Opposition members targeting the government on several issues, MLAs today maintained silence.         
	Legislative council chairman Arun Kumar also adjourned the House till Monday after it paid homage.                                                                                                                                                                           
